"""
Hardened Dual-Arm Probe — V1.

Built 2026-05-18 to lift the 6 operational conditions in
``Build_Docs/Architecture/DUAL_ARM_PROBE_PRINCIPLES.md`` from principles
honored-by-construction into preconditions enforced-by-code.

Wraps v11's machinery; does not re-implement arm evaluation. On top of v11
this module adds:

1. A frozen ``DualArmConfig`` declaring channels / routes / activation /
   selection. Construction-time validation rejects target-aware selection
   rules, non-`armW_falloff` activation, unknown route kinds, and
   ARM-N validity predicates whose signatures expose ARM-W fields.
2. A per-record 6-condition checklist + ``hardened_status`` derived
   strictly from the checklist. Only `(c1..c6)` all True and the record
   being inside an ARM-W-declared gap produces ``gap_resolved``.
3. Diagnostic-route capping: when any route is declared ``diagnostic`` the
   run is allowed (so audits can still record the data) but no record
   reaches ``gap_resolved``; all records carry
   ``underpromotion_reason=diagnostic_route_present``.
4. Same-route control opt-in: ``same_route_control=True`` lets ARM-W and
   ARM-N share a channel; without that flag, equal channels raise at
   construction.
5. A V4 validity stamp on the top-level result (defined/finite/observable/
   selectable/advanceable) keyed to the six conditions and the scan-level
   stability check.

This module is **eval-layer** only. It records design-time discipline; it
does not promote the dual-arm pattern into substrate. See
``DUAL_ARM_PROBE_PRINCIPLES.md`` "What these constraints are NOT".
"""
